    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it has flaws, but it feels like the \"flaws\" people talk about are just excuses for countries to do whatever they want without consequences. like, if the UN can't even stop systemic violence because of a veto, doesn't that make the whole structure fundamentally broken rather than just \"flawed\"? isn't the idea of its legitimacy kind of a myth at this point?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
